  "caption": "Figure 3. Avsunviroidae . Phylogenetic tree of members of the family Avsunviroidae. Trees were inferred by the neighbor-joining method using MEGA7 ( Kumar et al., 2016 ) with bootstrap values (1000 replicates). Reference sequences for each viroid species were aligned using MUSCLE (position 1 of each sequence corresponds to the nucleotide after the (+) self-cleavage site) with minor manual adjustments. Bootstrap values are reported at the nodes. Evolutionary distances were estimated according to the model of Jukes and Cantor ( Jukes and Cantor 1969 ) eliminating positions with less than 30% coverage. Viroids cluster according to their taxonomic position within the genera in the family. This phylogenetic tree and corresponding sequence alignment are available to download from the Resources page .",
